{"ts":"2026-06-27T01:24:31.996Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"1hlao1ad","input":{"summary":"I have resolved the TypeScript compilation/type-checking error reported during the Next.js build.\n\n### Investigation & Resolution Steps:\n1. **Identified the Issue:**\n   - The Next.js build failed during TypeScript compilation with the error:\n     `Type error: Module '\"./types\"' has no exported member 'BadgeState'.` in `./components/private-app/cards-metrics-badges.tsx`.\n2. **Analysis:**\n   - Inspected `components/private-app/cards-metrics-badges.tsx` where `BadgeState` was being imported.\n   - Checked the `StatusBadge` styling structure and mapped states, identifying the accepted values for `BadgeState` as `\"active\" | \"warning\" | \"error\" | \"stable\" | \"decoupled\"`.\n   - Inspected `components/private-app/types.ts` and confirmed `BadgeState` was missing from the file.\n3. **Applied the Fix:**\n   - Modified `components/private-app/types.ts` using the `editor` tool to export the correct union type definition:\n     `export type BadgeState = \"active\" | \"warning\" | \"error\" | \"stable\" | \"decoupled\";`\n4. **Validation Done:**\n   - Executed a targeted strict TypeScript compiler command on all private app components (`npx tsc components/private-app/*.tsx components/private-app/*.ts --noEmit --esModuleInterop --jsx react-jsx --skipLibCheck --target es6 --moduleResolution node`) which compiled successfully with zero errors.\n   - Executed the global strict compiler verification check (`npx tsc --noEmit`) which succeeded completely with zero errors across the entire codebase.\n\nThe fix is robust, correct, and strictly resolves the type error. No routing or landing page components were modified, adhering fully to the guardrails.","verified":true}}}
